text: George McGovern (1922–2012) was a U.S. Senator from South Dakota from 1963 to 1981. Senator McGovern may also refer to: *J. Raymond McGovern (1898–1974), New York State Senate *Patricia McGovern (fl. 1980s–2010s), Massachusetts State Senate *Peter McGovern (politician) (1845–1917), Minnesota State Senate
title: Senator McGovern (disambiguation)
